cts.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ENow%2C%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20new%20apartments%20and%20houses%20are%20in%20danger%20of%20not%20being%20built.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EPresident%20Donald%20Trump%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-federal-buyout-plan-works-resignation-pay-salary-rto-trump-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edismantled%20federal%20agencies%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdoge-department-of-government-efficiency%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eslashed%20spending%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20he's%20pledged%20to%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.whitehouse.gov%2Farticles%2F2025%2F05%2Fweek-15-wins-president-trumps-100th-day-marked-by-more-success%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egut%20the%20weaponized%20deep%20state%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20has%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-housing-plan-federal-lands-tax-incentives-mortgage-rates-ubs-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evowed%20to%20ease%20the%20housing%20shortage%3C%2Fa%3E%20across%20the%20nation.%20One%20promise%20may%20come%20at%20the%20expense%20of%20the%20other%20in%20the%20case%20of%20one%20agency's%20retrenchment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20February%2C%20his%20administration%20sought%20to%20take%20back%20%2420%20billion%20awarded%20by%20the%20Environmental%20Protection%20Agency%20during%20Joe%20Biden's%20presidency%20to%20fund%20decarbonization%20projects%20around%20the%20country.%20The%20head%20of%20the%20EPA%20has%20justified%20the%20clawback%20attempt%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.epa.gov%2Fnewsreleases%2Fadministrator-zeldin-terminates-biden-harris-20b-gold-bar-grants%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunproven%20accusations%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20grants%20were%20marred%20by%20%26quot%3Bprogrammatic%20fraud%2C%20waste%2C%20and%20abuse.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20new%20apartments%20and%20houses%20that%20were%20expected%20to%20be%20financed%20with%20a%20portion%20of%20the%20EPA%20money%20are%20now%20in%20danger%20of%20not%20being%20built%2C%20nonprofit%20groups%20who%20were%20granted%20the%20funding%20say.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EClimate%20United%2C%20a%20coalition%20that%20received%20roughly%20%247%20billion%20of%20the%20money%20%E2%80%94%20known%20as%20the%20Greenhouse%20Gas%20Reduction%20Fund%20%E2%80%94%20is%20suing%20the%20EPA%20along%20with%20other%20awardees%20over%20the%20withheld%20funding.%20The%20nonprofit%20estimates%20that%20about%2030%2C000%20single-family%20homes%20and%20another%2030%2C000%20apartment%20units%20were%20to%20be%20built%20with%20some%20of%20the%20funds%20that%20it%20and%20another%20group%20were%20set%20to%20administer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20significant%20part%20of%20the%20strategy%20focused%20on%20building%20not%20only%20new%20housing%20but%20new%20affordable%20and%20workforce%20housing%2C%26quot%3B%20Beth%20Bafford%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20Climate%20United%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20varied%20estimates%20on%20how%20many%20new%20homes%20are%20needed%20in%20the%20US.%20Freddie%20Mac%2C%20a%20mortgage%20lending%20agency%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.freddiemac.com%2Fresearch%2Fforecast%2F20241126-us-economy-remains-resilient-with-strong-q3-growth%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecalculated%20recently%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20country%20is%20short%20about%203.7%20million%20units.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20homes%20that%20might%20be%20built%20with%20money%20from%20the%20GGRF%20would%20be%20just%20a%20small%20contribution%20toward%20that%20huge%20need%2C%20the%20fund's%20proponents%20say%20the%20money%20would%20go%20to%20a%20particularly%20impactful%20segment%20of%20the%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBafford%20said%20that%20the%20focus%20of%20the%20GGRF%20money%20was%20on%20housing%20development%20projects%20in%20a%20part%20of%20the%20market%20with%20a%20lack%20of%20private%20sector%20financing%20options%3A%20affordable%20projects%20using%20energy-efficient%20systems%20and%20materials%20that%20are%20environmentally%20sustainable%20while%20helping%20mitigate%20utility%20costs%20for%20residents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20see%20massive%20gaps%20in%20the%20financial%20markets%2C%20and%20this%20program%20was%20built%20to%20address%20some%20of%20those%20gaps%2C%26quot%3B%20Bafford%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20spokesperson%20for%20Climate%20United%20said%20it%20had%20%26quot%3Bdisbursed%20%2425%20million%20in%20loans%20and%20committed%20over%20%24500%20million%20in%20loans%20before%20the%20EPA%20terminated%20our%20grant%20agreement%20without%20warning.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUnlike%20the%20Biden-Haris%20administration%2C%20this%20EPA%20is%20committed%20to%20being%20an%20exceptional%20steward%20of%20taxpayer%20dollars%2C%26quot%3B%20an%20unnamed%20spokesperson%20from%20the%20EPA%20responded%20in%20an%20email.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20spokesperson%20said%20the%20GGRF's%20termination%20was%20%26quot%3Bbased%20on%20substantial%20concerns%26quot%3B%20over%20its%20%26quot%3Bintegrity%2C%20the%20award%20process%2C%20and%20programmatic%20waste%20and%20abuse%2C%20which%20collectively%20undermine%20the%20fundamental%20goals%20and%20statutory%20objectives%20of%20the%20award.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22227514b5-91c4-4d05-bf54-e94570888671%5C%22%3ESome%20developers%20are%20already%20feeling%20the%20impact%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20impacts%20of%20the%20freeze%20have%20already%20been%20felt%20by%20some%20developers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMegan%20Lasch%2C%20the%20chief%20executive%20of%20O-SDA%20Industries%2C%20a%20for-profit%20builder%20of%20affordable%20housing%20based%20in%20Austin%2C%20said%20the%20EPA's%20clawback%20attempt%20made%20her%20reshuffle%20a%20portion%20of%20the%20financing%20package%20she%20had%20been%20arranging%20for%20a%2090-unit%20affordable%20apartment%20project%20her%20firm%20is%20developing%20in%20Fort%20Worth%2C%20Texas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20roughly%20%2437%20million%20development%20involves%20renovating%20801%20West%20Shaw%20St.%2C%20a%20historic%20building%20with%2045%20rental%20apartments%2C%20erecting%20an%20additional%2045%20units%20on%20land%20adjacent%20to%20the%20property%2C%20and%20building%20a%20pre-K%20facility.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELasch%20said%20she%20had%20arranged%20to%20use%20some%20%243%20million%20of%20GGRF%20money%20for%20the%20project%20from%20the%20Local%20Initiatives%20Support%20Corporation%2C%20a%20member%20of%20Power%20Forward%20Communities%2C%20a%20coalition%20that%20received%20%242%20billion%20of%20the%20EPA%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20GGRF%20money%20was%20held%20up%2C%20Lasch%20said%20that%20she%20found%20a%20replacement%20loan%20but%20that%20the%20new%20funding%20is%20more%20costly%2C%20carrying%20a%20roughly%204.5%25%20interest%20rate%20versus%20the%20GGRF%20loan's%20roughly%201%25%20rate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20patch%20was%20not%20pretty%2C%26quot%3B%20Lasch%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20affordable%20housing%20projects%20often%20have%20thin%20margins%20and%20require%20deeply%20discounted%20financing%20to%20work.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20going%20to%20be%20ultimately%20a%20lot%20of%20projects%20that%20will%20just%20go%20by%20the%20wayside%20because%20they're%20not%20able%20to%20come%20up%20with%20a%20patch.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20801%20West%20Shaw%20St.%20building%20is%20set%20to%20offer%20rents%20that%20are%20affordable%20for%20residents%20who%20earn%20between%2030%25%20and%2060%25%20of%20the%20area's%20median%20income%2C%20Lasch%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDamon%20Burns%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20Finance%20New%20Orleans%2C%20a%20public%20trust%20that%20helps%20fund%20and%20develop%20affordable%20housing%20in%20its%20namesake%20city%2C%20said%20that%20his%20organization%20had%20been%20allocated%20%245%20million%20from%20the%20Coalition%20for%20Green%20Capital%2C%20which%20received%20%245%20billion%20of%20GGRF%20money%20from%20the%20EPA.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFinance%20New%20Orleans%20was%20seeking%20to%20use%20about%20%241%20million%20of%20that%20%245%20million%20it%20was%20to%20receive%20in%20combination%20with%20%241.5%20million%20of%20other%20funds%20it%20holds%20to%20build%20six%20or%20seven%20new%20homes%20with%20net-zero%20emissions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUsing%20GGRF%20money%20to%20augment%20his%20organization's%20funding%20pipeline%20to%20build%20more%20housing%20was%20a%20model%20that%20Burns%20said%20he%20had%20hoped%20to%20scale.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20the%20prospect%20of%20having%20the%20GGRF%20money%20withdrawn%20was%20daunting%20because%20New%20Orleans%20is%20%26quot%3Balready%20a%20financially%20constrained%20city.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20is%20a%20huge%20concern%20that%20the%20disinvestment%20of%20the%20federal%20government%20will%20have%20an%20impact%20on%20all%20of%20our%20communities%2C%26quot%3B%20Burns%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20means%20less%20mortgages%20for%20homeowners.%20It%20means%20less%20capital%20for%20developers.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d84572d6-ac99-4bad-99c5-e2bf64a1e3ff%5C%22%3EA%20climate-focused%20financing%20initiative%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20GGRF%20was%20created%20with%20%2427%20billion%20of%20federal%20funds%20from%20the%20Biden%20administration's%20Inflation%20Reduction%20Act%2C%20which%20Congress%20passed%20in%202022.%20Some%20%2420%20billion%20of%20that%20amount%20was%20awarded%20to%20Climate%20United%2C%20Power%20Forward%20Communities%2C%20the%20Coalition%20for%20Green%20Capital%2C%20and%20other%20groups%20for%20various%20climate-focused%20financing%20initiatives.%20The%20remaining%20%247%20billion%20went%20toward%20a%20federal%20program%20to%20fund%20residential%20solar%20energy%20installation%20projects.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20December%2C%20Project%20Veritas%2C%20a%20conservative%20media%20organization%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DCblV6EwzKxg%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epublished%20a%20video%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20showed%20a%20former%20EPA%20official%20suggesting%20that%20the%20agency%2C%20under%20Biden%2C%20had%20fast-tracked%20its%20award%20of%20the%20money%20in%20anticipation%20that%20the%20incoming%20Trump%20administration%20might%20seek%20to%20scuttle%20the%20program.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%227702%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Lee%20Zeldin%20testifying%20before%20a%20Senate%20subcommittee%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F682791b3c6ad288d1481350a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225134%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELee%20Zeldin%2C%20the%20EPA%20administrator.%3Cp%3ETom%20Williams%2FCQ-Roll%20Call%2C%20Inc%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20video%2C%20the%20official%20said%3A%20%26quot%3BIt%20truly%20feels%20like%20we're%20on%20the%20Titanic%20and%20we're%20throwing%20gold%20bars%20off%20the%20edge.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELee%20Zeldin%2C%20a%20former%20Long%20Island%2C%20New%20York%2C%20congressman%20whom%20Trump%20appointed%20as%20the%20head%20of%20the%20EPA%20in%20January%2C%20cited%20the%20video%20as%20evidence%20of%20misconduct%20in%20the%20allocation%20of%20the%20funds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOne%20of%20my%20very%20top%20priorities%20at%20EPA%20is%20to%20be%20an%20excellent%20steward%20of%20your%20hard-earned%20tax%20dollars%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Fepaleezeldin%2Fstatus%2F1889840040622321778%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EZeldin%20said%20in%20a%20video%3C%2Fa%3E%20posted%20on%20his%20X%20account%20in%20February.%20%26quot%3BThe%20'gold%20bars'%20were%20your%20tax%20dollars%2C%20and%20tossing%20them%20off%20the%20Titanic%20meant%20the%20Biden%20administration%20knew%20they%20were%20wasting%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZeldin%20has%20ordered%20the%20termination%20of%20the%20GGRF.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20March%2C%20Climate%20United%20sued%20the%20EPA%20and%20Citibank%2C%20the%20financial%20intermediary%20for%20the%20%2420%20billion%2C%20in%20the%20federal%20district%20court%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20over%20their%20refusal%20to%20release%20the%20money.%20Power%20Forward%20and%20the%20Coalition%20for%20Green%20Capital%20have%20joined%20the%20suit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20EPA%20lost%20the%20initial%20argument%20for%20the%20case%20but%20has%20brought%20its%20complaint%20to%20the%20Court%20of%20Appeals%20for%20the%20District%20of%20Columbia%20Circuit%2C%20where%20it%20won%20a%20preliminary%20order%20in%20April%20to%20freeze%20the%20money%20as%20its%20appeal%20is%20being%20considered.%20The%20next%20hearing%20in%20the%20case%20is%20scheduled%20for%20Monday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e589b13a-53b7-4efa-af6c-2396980b9826%5C%22%3E'Every%20single%20project%20in%20the%20country%20is%20looking%20for%20gap%20funding'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Climate%20United%20estimated%20that%20terminating%20the%20GGRF%20would%20put%20roughly%2060%2C000%20homes%20at%20risk%2C%20other%20parties%20involved%20in%20the%20financing%20program%20say%20that%20number%20could%20be%20even%20greater.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20has%20been%20a%20sharp%20increase%20in%20the%20number%20of%20housing%20developers%20interested%20in%20tapping%20financing%20from%20the%20GGRF%2C%20said%20Shaun%20Donovan%2C%20the%20president%20and%20CEO%20of%20the%20nonprofit%20housing%20lender%20Enterprise%20Community%20Partners.%20He%20was%20a%20secretary%20of%20the%20Department%20of%20Housing%20and%20Urban%20Development%20in%20the%20Obama%20administration.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDonovan%20attributed%20that%20interest%20to%20growing%20construction%20costs%20from%20inflation%20and%20tariffs%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftariffs-trump-steel-aluminum-tiles-development-real-estate-construction-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewhich%20have%20driven%20up%20the%20price%20of%20building%20materials%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Those%20overruns%20have%20punched%20holes%20in%20the%20budgets%20of%20a%20host%20of%20development%20projects%20that%20builders%20have%20scrambled%20to%20fill.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEvery%20single%20project%20in%20the%20country%20is%20looking%20for%20gap%20funding%2C%26quot%3B%20Donovan%20said.%20%26quot%3BWhat%20this%20GGRF%20money%20can%20do%20is%20to%20be%20that%20last%20dollar%20in%2C%20right%3F%20So%20even%20if%20it's%20only%205%25%20or%2010%25%20of%20the%20project.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20spokesperson%20for%20Enterprise%20said%20that%20it%20had%20received%20inquiries%20for%20about%20%241.2%20billion%20of%20financing%20in%20recent%20months%20for%20a%20collection%20of%20projects%20totaling%2018%2C426%20units.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20concern%20is%20that%20what%20this%20and%20other%20efforts%20to%20cut%20housing%20programs%20will%20do%20is%20make%20it%20impossible%20for%20the%20president%20to%20meet%20his%20goal%20of%20reducing%20housing%20costs%2C%26quot%3B%20Donovan%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhousing-projects-epa-climate-financing-trump-2025-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1747645261000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F682793043fe8d39283661f4b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhousing-projects-epa-climate-financing-trump-2025-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20EPA%20says%20Biden-era%20grants%20were%20marred%20by%20%26quot%3Bwaste%20and%20abuse.%26quot%3B%20Nonprofit%20groups%20say%20a%20clawback%20of%20the%20funds%20would%20derail%20projects%20to%20build%20housing.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22dgeiger%40businessinsider.com%20(Daniel%20Geiger)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A27%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhousing-projects-epa-climate-financing-trump-2025-5%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Go%20go%20go%3A'%20Bankers%20are%20telling%20startups%20to%20get%20their%20IPOs%20done%20fast%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221936%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Chime%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5c5e3ba4dde8674e877c4562%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221290%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EChime%20Co-founders%20Chris%20Britt%20and%20Ryan%20King.%20The%20digital%20banking%20app%20filed%20to%20go%20public%20this%20week%20after%20previously%20pausing%20its%20IPO%20plans%20on%20President%20Donald%20Trump's%20tariffs.%3Cp%3EChime%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20markets%20have%20relaxed%20after%20Trump's%20tariffs%20scare%2C%20and%20companies%20are%20racing%20to%20go%20public%20again.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EStartups%20like%20Chime%20and%20Hinge%20Health%20resumed%20their%20IPO%20plans%20this%20week%20after%20previous%20delays.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBankers%20are%20telling%20IPO%20hopefuls%20to%20capitalize%20on%20the%20market's%20stability%20%E2%80%94%20knowing%20it%20may%20not%20last.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIPOs%20are%20back%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0just%20a%20month%20after%20a%20sudden%20market%20slump%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fipo-comeback-victim-trump-tariffs-stock-market-crash-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eforced%20tech%20companies%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20put%20their%20public%20market%20debuts%20on%20hold.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20time%2C%20bankers%20are%20telling%20companies%20to%20rush%20out%20while%20they%20still%20can.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you're%20trying%20to%20get%20public%2C%20now%20is%20the%20time%20to%20'go%20go%20go'%20before%20something%20else%20happens%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20healthcare%20banker%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20The%20banker%20requested%20anonymity%20because%20they%20weren't%20authorized%20to%20speak%20to%20the%20press.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20announced%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcategory%2Ftariffs%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esweeping%20tariffs%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20imports%20from%20other%20countries%20on%20April%202%2C%20the%20markets%20panicked.%20The%20chaos%20forced%20companies%20from%20the%20payments%20lender%20Klarna%20to%20the%20physical%20therapy%20startup%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhinge-health-delaying-planned-ipo-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EHinge%20Health%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20put%20their%20long-awaited%20IPO%20plans%20on%20hold.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20in%20the%20past%20month%2C%20a%20number%20of%20changes%2C%20including%20Trump's%20rollbacks%20of%20the%20most%20severe%20tariffs%20and%20assurances%20he%20would%20not%20fire%20Federal%20Reserve%20Chair%20Jerome%20Powell%2C%20all%20but%20erased%20that%20market%20drop.%20The%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20is%20now%20up%20about%201%25%20since%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20year%2C%20a%20nearly%2019%25%20increase%20from%20its%20April%20lows.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20IPOs%20on%20the%20table%20again%2C%20companies%20are%20hustling%20to%20complete%20those%20deals%20while%20the%20market%20stability%20holds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEToro%2C%20the%20Israeli%20trading%20platform%2C%20made%20its%20public%20debut%20on%20Wednesday%20via%20a%20SPAC%20merger%20and%20saw%20its%20shares%20pop%20on%20the%20Nasdaq%2C%20opening%2034%25%20above%20the%20IPO%20price%20and%20valuing%20the%20company%20at%20nearly%20%245.2%20billion%20by%20Friday.%20Hinge%20Health%20resumed%20its%20own%20IPO%20plans%20by%20kicking%20off%20its%20road%20show%20Tuesday%2C%20aiming%20for%20a%20valuation%20of%20up%20to%20%242.6%20billion.%20Digital%20banking%20app%20Chime%20and%20diabetes%20care%20startup%20Omada%20Health%20also%20filed%20to%20go%20public%20in%20May.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20markets%20have%20bounced%20back%20quickly%20after%20Trump%20rolled%20back%20most%20tariffs%20in%20part%20because%20investor%20appetites%20didn't%20go%20away%2C%20said%20Tom%20Johnson%2C%20global%20cohead%20of%20capital%20markets%20at%20Barclays.%20(Barclays%20is%20an%20underwriter%20on%20Hinge%20Health%20and%20Omada%20Health's%20planned%20IPOs.)%20Companies%20are%20being%20encouraged%20to%20seize%20on%20that%20improvement%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BKnowing%20that%20we're%20perhaps%20going%20to%20be%20living%20in%20a%20world%20with%20a%20bit%20more%20volatility%2C%20you've%20got%20to%20be%20thinking%20about%20going%20when%20you%20can%2C%26quot%3B%20Johnson%20said.%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227d495413-9712-4f72-beb3-eee2bdcdc477%5C%22%3EReleasing%20pent-up%20IPO%20demand%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBankers%20are%20looking%20at%20a%20number%20of%20signals%20that%20suggest%20companies%20could%20see%20successful%20IPOs%20right%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20importantly%2C%20the%20volatility%20index%20has%20cooled%2C%20signaling%20calmer%20markets.%20VIX%2C%20a%20measure%20of%20market%20volatility%20often%20called%20the%20stock%20market's%20fear%20gauge%2C%20denotes%20high%20volatility%20at%20values%20of%2030%20or%20more%2C%20while%20values%20of%2020%20or%20below%20signal%20more%20stability.%20The%20VIX%20index%20hit%20painful%20highs%20of%2052%20on%20April%208.%20As%20of%20Friday%2C%20the%20index%20has%20dropped%20to%2017.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20reduced%20volatility%2C%20combined%20with%20better%20market%20performance%2C%20has%20allowed%20public%20investors%20to%20stop%20playing%20defense%20with%20their%20existing%20portfolios%20and%20consider%20new%20buys.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20steadier%20supply%20chains%20for%20most%20industries%20and%20fewer%20market%20shocks%2C%20companies%20and%20investors%20are%20also%20finding%20it%20easier%20to%20agree%20on%20fair%20pricing%2C%20a%20key%20ingredient%20for%20a%20successful%20IPO.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBoards%20are%20now%20talking%20about%20the%20IPO%20option%20as%20being%20attractive%20and%20something%20that%20they%20want%20to%20proactively%20seek%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Jimmy%20Williams%2C%20a%20senior%20banker%20at%20Jefferies%20who%20worked%20on%20the%20eToro%20deal.%20%26quot%3BThe%20backlog%20of%20private%20companies%20waiting%20to%20go%20public%20right%20now%20is%20one%20of%20the%20longest%20we've%20ever%20seen%20because%20we've%20had%20such%20a%20historic%20drought%20the%20last%20three%20years.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226308%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Hinge%20Health%20cofounders%20Daniel%20Perez%2C%20CEO%2C%20and%20Gabriel%20Mecklenburg%2C%20executive%20chairman.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6827515268a2929008018898%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224731%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EHinge%20Health%20launched%20the%20road%20show%20for%20its%20IPO%20this%20week.%20The%20physical%20therapy%20startup%20has%20been%20signaling%20its%20intentions%20to%20go%20public%20for%20several%20years.%3Cp%3EHinge%20Health%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2297714614-7188-46c2-a8ff-c74cc4df0b85%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ENo%20guarantee%20of%20sunny%20skies%20ahead%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20recent%20market%20improvements%2C%20Barclays'%20head%20of%20Americas%20equity%20capital%20markets%2C%20Robert%20Stowe%2C%20said%20it's%20reasonable%20to%20expect%20higher%20political%20volatility%20for%20the%20foreseeable%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20conversations%20are%20harder%20than%20they've%20been%20historically.%20It's%20harder%20to%20predict%20even%20the%20next%20day%2C%20let%20alone%20the%20two%20weeks%20you%20need%20for%20a%20typical%20IPO%20roadshow%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20all%20of%20the%20companies%20previously%20rumored%20to%20be%20on%20the%20precipice%20of%20IPOs%20have%20come%20back%20to%20market%20yet.%20As%20of%20May%2015%2C%20online%20payments%20company%20Klarna%20and%20ticket%20marketplace%20StubHub%2C%20which%20both%20reportedly%20delayed%20their%20IPO%20plans%20in%20April%20due%20to%20the%20stock%20sell-off%2C%20haven't%20publicly%20reupped%20those%20efforts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENeither%20has%20Medline%2C%20a%20surgical%20equipment%20company%20backed%20by%20private%20equity%20firms%20Blackstone%20and%20Carlyle%2C%20which%20said%20in%20December%20it%20had%20confidentially%20filed%20its%20S-1.%20Medline%20had%20been%20planning%20a%20spring%202025%20IPO%20until%20Liberation%20Day%20tariffs%20forced%20an%20indefinite%20delay%2C%20per%20the%20Financial%20Times.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20clear%20yet%20which%20of%20these%20companies%2C%20if%20any%2C%20will%20resume%20their%20IPO%20efforts%20in%20the%20current%20market.%20Medline%2C%20for%20one%2C%20still%20stands%20to%20be%20significantly%20affected%20by%20the%20tariffs%2C%20since%20the%20company%20manufactures%20much%20of%20its%20supplies%20in%20China.%20Most%20imports%20from%20China%20now%20face%20a%2030%25%20tariff%2C%20at%20least%20for%20the%20next%2090%20days%2C%20while%20the%20US%20and%20China%20attempt%20to%20negotiate%20a%20long-term%20trade%20deal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpokespeople%20for%20Klarna%20and%20StubHub%20said%20the%20companies%20don't%20have%20any%20information%20to%20share%20on%20their%20IPO%20plans.%20Medline%20didn't%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment%20for%20this%20story.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPrivate%20investors%20may%20not%20be%20able%20to%20take%20advantage%20of%20the%20market%20upswing%20by%20cashing%20out%20at%20a%20company's%20IPO%2C%20either.%20Insiders%20are%20frequently%20subject%20to%20lock-up%20periods%2C%20wherein%20investors%20have%20to%20wait%20from%2090%20and%20180%20days%20after%20the%20IPO%20to%20sell%20their%20shares%2C%20sometimes%20even%20longer.%20Given%20how%20much%20the%20market%20has%20fluctuated%20this%20year%2C%20investors%20can't%20be%20sure%20that%20shares%20will%20continue%20ticking%20up%20for%20the%20next%20six%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20it%20may%20be%20worth%20it%20to%20get%20an%20exit%20on%20the%20books%20while%20the%20market%20fundamentals%20are%20favorable%2C%20particularly%20for%20mature%20companies%20like%20Omada%20Health%20founded%20more%20than%20a%20decade%20ago%2C%20and%20offer%20an%20opportunity%20for%20investors%20to%20get%20the%20returns%20they've%20been%20waiting%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20is%20more%20impetus%20to%20get%20the%20first%20deal%20done%20and%20get%20the%20company%20listed%2C%20give%20the%20stock%20a%20chance%20to%20trade%2C%20and%20then%20the%20owners%20can%20be%20more%20nimble%20with%20the%20balance%20that%20they're%20holding%2C%26quot%3B%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3EStowe%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20other%20companies%2C%20especially%20those%20that%20could%20be%20more%20vulnerable%20to%20policy%20changes%2C%20bankers%20are%20advising%20a%20%26quot%3Bwait%20and%20see%26quot%3B%20approach%2C%20watching%20how%20this%20next%20set%20of%20IPOs%20performs%20and%20continuing%20to%20evaluate%20emerging%20political%20risks%2C%20said%20Phil%20Capen%2C%20a%20managing%20director%20of%20equity%20capital%20markets%20at%20Deutsche%20Bank.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20market%20is%20getting%20better%2C%20but%20there's%20still%20a%20lot%20of%20uncertainty%20out%20there.%20If%20you%20don't%20need%20to%20go%2C%20and%20you%20can%20be%20patient%2C%20I%20think%20there%20are%20a%20number%20of%20companies%20that%20are%20just%20waiting%20to%20find%20the%20right%20window%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbankers-telling-startups-get-ipos-done-fast-2025-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1747645201000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68279d0b3fe8d39283662193%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbankers-telling-startups-get-ipos-done-fast-2025-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22As%20the%20public%20markets%20improve%2C%20tech%20companies%20are%20rushing%20to%20IPO%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0knowing%20more%20political%20volatility%20could%20be%20around%20the%20corner.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22rtorrence%40businessinsider.com%20(Rebecca%20Torrence%2CBen%20Bergman)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbankers-telling-startups-get-ipos-done-fast-2025-5%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Big%20Tech%20is%20winning%20the%20battle%20of%20the%20bulge%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20google%2C%20Microsoft%2C%20and%20Intel%20logo%20being%20flattened%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F682799463fe8d39283662090%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMicrosoft%20CEO%20Satya%20Nadella%3Cp%3EGetty%20images%3B%20Tyler%20Le%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EMicrosoft%20is%20among%20the%20latest%20to%20cut%20middle%20management%20jobs.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ETech%20giants%20like%20Intel%2C%20Amazon%2C%20and%20Google%20are%20also%20flattening%20structures%20for%20efficiency.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EExperts%20warn%20that%20while%20flattening%20can%20speed%20decisions%2C%20it%20is%20possible%20to%20take%20it%20too%20far.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ECompanies%20are%20shedding%20bloated%20layers%20of%20management%20in%20an%20attempt%20to%20reduce%20bureaucracy.%20Some%20employees%20are%20applauding%20the%20move%2C%20known%20as%20flattening%20the%20middle%2C%20in%20the%20hopes%20of%20getting%20faster%20and%20boosting%20efficiency.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMicrosoft%20said%20Tuesday%20it's%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-plans-to-cut-thousands-of-employees-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20slashing%20around%206%2C000%20employees.%3C%2Fa%3E%20While%20the%20days%20since%20have%20made%20it%20clear%20many%20of%20those%20cut%20were%20individual%20contributor-level%20engineers%2C%20executives%20previously%20told%20BI%20one%20motivation%20behind%20the%20recent%20cuts%20was%20to%20increase%20managers'%20%26quot%3Bspan%20of%20control%2C%26quot%3B%20or%20the%20number%20of%20reports%20per%20manager.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fintel-new-ceo-organizational-change-rto-layoffs-kpis-meetings-earnings-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIntel%3C%2Fa%3E%20announced%20a%20great%20flattening%20last%20month%2C%20emphasizing%20more%20time%20in%20the%20office%2C%20less%20admin%2C%20and%20leaner%20teams.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20best%20leaders%20get%20the%20most%20done%20with%20the%20fewest%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20the%20chip%20giant's%20new%20CEO%2C%20Lip-Bu%20Tan%2C%20in%20a%20memo%20to%20staff.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-charlie-bell-amazon-aws-cloud-computing-azure-cybersecurity-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmazon%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20also%20increased%20the%20ratio%20of%20individual%20contributors%20to%20managers.%20They%20call%20it%20a%20%26quot%3Bbuilder%20ratio.%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-ceo-company-cut-manager-vp-roles-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20Google%3C%2Fa%3E%20CEO%20Sundar%20Pichai%20told%20staff%20late%20last%20year%20that%20the%20company%20cut%20vice%20president%20and%20manager%20roles%20by%2010%25%20as%20part%20of%20an%20efficiency%20push.%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-layoffs-zuckerberg-productivity-year-efficiency-innovation-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20Meta%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20been%20at%20it%20for%20years%2C%20with%20CEO%20Mark%20Zuckerberg%20writing%20in%20a%202023%20memo%2C%20%26quot%3Bflatter%20is%20faster.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20risk%20is%20that%20these%20companies%20cut%20too%20many%20managers%2C%20leaving%20the%20remaining%20folks%20with%20too%20many%20direct%20reports.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20for%20now%2C%20it%20appears%20to%20be%20a%20risk%20companies%20are%20willing%20to%20take.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222c8d6acb-dc3d-469a-9688-3281c1554d21%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EAgility%20and%20expertise%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20logic%20of%20cutting%20from%20the%20middle%20to%20speed%20up%20is%20sound%2C%20management%20experts%20say.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20can't%20go%20faster%20and%20be%20more%20connected%20to%20a%20larger%20ecosystem%20if%20you're%20having%20to%20go%20up%20and%20down%20a%20hierarchy%20for%20every%20decision%2C%26quot%3B%20Deborah%20Ancona%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20management%20at%20Massachusetts%20Institute%20of%20Technology%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20some%20companies%20have%20been%20trying%20for%20decades%20to%20zap%20management%20layers%2C%20there's%20a%20new%20urgency%20to%20do%20so.%20Businesses%20exist%20in%20%26quot%3Ban%20exponentially%20changing%20world%2C%26quot%3B%20Ancona%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdell-reorganizes-top-ranks-asks-senior-managers-lead-more-staff-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDell%3C%2Fa%3E%20executives%20explained%20this%20to%20employees%20earlier%20this%20month%2C%20when%20they%20began%20reorganizing%20managers%20to%20have%20more%20direct%20reports.%20The%20company%2C%20whose%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdell-employee-numbers-decline-by-25000-since-2023-rto-layoffs-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehead%20count%20has%20dropped%20by%2025%2C000%20in%20two%20years%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20also%20pointed%20to%20the%20influx%20of%20artificial%20intelligence%20as%20a%20reason%20it%20needed%20to%20move%20faster.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIdeally%2C%20companies%20would%20remove%20layers%20and%20spread%20decision-making%20throughout%20the%20organization%20so%20that%20those%20closest%20to%20customers%20or%20technology%2C%20for%20example%2C%20could%20generate%20ideas%20and%20make%20decisions%2C%20Ancona%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou're%20kind%20of%20flipping%20the%20organization%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BRather%20than%20all%20the%20ideas%20coming%20from%20on%20high%2C%20you%20have%20entrepreneurial%20leaders%20who%20are%20lower%20down%20in%20the%20organization%20coming%20up%20with%20new%20ideas.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBayer%20CEO%20Bill%20Anderson%20is%20leery%20of%20having%20to%20run%20everything%20up%20the%20chain%3Cstrong%3E.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20After%20taking%20over%20the%20German%20biotech%20company%20in%202023%2C%20he%20began%20implementing%20what%20he%20calls%20a%20%26quot%3Bdynamic%20shared%20ownership%26quot%3B%20setup%20that%20has%20cut%20thousands%20of%20managers.%20Staffers%20come%20together%20in%20%26quot%3Bmini%20networks%26quot%3B%20for%2090-day%20stretches%20to%20work%20on%20projects.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20hire%20highly%20educated%2C%20trained%20people%2C%20and%20then%20we%20put%20them%20in%20these%20environments%20with%20rules%20and%20procedures%20and%20eight%20layers%20of%20hierarchy%2C%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbayer-bill-anderson-ceo-corporate-hierarchy-get-rid-of-bosses-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20Anderson%20previously%20told%20BI%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BThen%20we%20wonder%20why%20big%20companies%20are%20so%20lame%20most%20of%20the%20time.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220d1445f9-687a-4e6a-9c25-86ba74a545aa%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EFewer%20managers%2C%20more%20reporting%2C%20more%20meetings%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20middle%20managers%20are%20cut%20and%20layers%20condensed%2C%20inevitably%2C%20more%20workers%20report%20to%20fewer%20managers.%20The%20logistics%20of%20that%20vary%2C%20and%20the%20success%20in%20terms%20of%20morale%20has%20a%20lot%20to%20do%20with%20the%20starting%20point.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmazon%20started%20flattening%20last%20year.%20In%20September%2C%20CEO%20Andy%20Jassy%20ordered%20a%2015%25%20increase%20in%20the%20ratio%20of%20individual%20contributors%20to%20managers%20by%20March.%20BI%20reported%20that%20senior%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-plan-cut-managers-aws-internal-guidelines-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20Amazon%20Web%20Services%20managers%20received%20a%20memo%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20January%20instructing%20them%20to%20restrict%20high-level%20hiring%20and%20increase%20their%20number%20of%20direct%20reports.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20Amazon%20spokesperson%20told%20BI%20at%20the%20time%20that%20the%20memo%20may%20have%20been%20intended%20for%20one%20team%2C%20but%20does%20not%20apply%20to%20the%20company%20at%20large.%20The%20Amazon%20spokesperson%20also%20referenced%20a%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aboutamazon.com%2Fnews%2Fcompany-news%2Fceo-andy-jassy-latest-update-on-amazon-return-to-office-manager-team-ratio%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20September%20memo%20from%20Jassy%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20importance%20of%20reducing%20management%20layers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20AWS%20manager%20told%20BI%20this%20month%20that%20the%20flatter%20structure%20has%20since%20put%20more%20burden%20on%20employees%20on%20her%20team%20to%20report%20on%20what%20they're%20doing%20day-to-day%2C%20in%20addition%20to%20their%20actual%20work%2C%20since%20managers%20have%20less%20time%20to%20inspect%20individuals'%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPlus%2C%20this%20manager%20said%20they%20are%20spending%20more%20time%20in%20meetings%20as%20they%20took%20on%20a%20more%20diverse%20group%20of%20direct%20reports.%20The%20Amazon%20spokesperson%20also%20emphasized%20that%20the%20individual%20employee's%20anecdote%20does%20not%20represent%20the%20company%20as%20a%20whole.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYvonne%20Lee-Hawkins%20was%20assigned%2021%20direct%20reports%20when%20she%20worked%20for%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fquit-amazon-manager-burned-out-from-employees-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20Amazon's%20human%20resources%3C%2Fa%3E.%20She%20told%20BI%20that%20she%20had%20to%20quickly%20learn%20new%20skills%20to%20handle%20the%20load%2C%20like%20asynchronous%20work%20strategies%2C%20but%20her%20teams'%20performance%20suffered%20as%20her%20number%20of%20reports%20grew%20from%2011%20to%2021%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWeekly%20one-on-ones%20%E2%80%94%20the%20subject%20of%20much%20debate%20among%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-ceo-mark-zuckerberg-management-style-direct-reports-delegation-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etech%20titans%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20became%20impossible%2C%20and%20she%20had%20to%20cut%20them%20in%20half.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20Microsoft%2C%20a%20half-dozen%20employees%20who%20spoke%20to%20BI%20about%20the%20manager%20flattening%20trend%20generally%20regarded%20it%20as%20a%20positive%20step%20to%20eliminate%20inefficient%20and%20unnecessary%20levels%20of%20managers.%20Some%20managers%20have%20as%20few%20as%20one%20or%20two%20reports.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMicrosoft%20ended%20up%20with%20many%20management%20layers%2C%20the%20people%20said%2C%20because%20it%20often%20tried%20to%20reward%20good%20engineers%20by%20promoting%20them%20to%20become%20managers.%20Often%2C%20those%20engineers-turned-managers%20still%20spent%20most%20of%20their%20time%20in%20the%20codebase%20and%20weren't%20very%20effective%20as%20managers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20larger%20groups%20of%20direct%20reports%20often%20work%20better%20for%20senior%20employees%2C%20who%20need%20less%20one-on-one%20time%20and%20can%20do%20more%20things%20in%20a%20group%20setting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Microsoft%20spokesperson%20did%20not%20comment%20when%20asked%20about%20these%20factors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGary%20Hamel%2C%20a%20visiting%20professor%20at%20London%20Business%20School%20who%20lives%20in%20Silicon%20Valley%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20pushing%20managers%20to%20take%20on%20more%20direct%20reports%20can%20reduce%20micromanaging%2C%20a%20common%20bane%20of%20corporate%20existence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20managers%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20to%20oversee%2C%20it%20pushes%20them%20to%20hire%20people%20they%20trust%2C%20mentor%20rather%20than%20manage%2C%20and%20give%20up%20a%20%26quot%3Bpretty%20big%20dose%26quot%3B%20of%20their%20authority.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThose%20are%20all%20hugely%20positive%20things%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20even%20if%20they%20require%20%26quot%3Ba%20fairly%20dramatic%20change%26quot%3B%20in%20how%20managers%20see%20their%20role.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226be62388-29cd-4630-bcae-1e5e2bf207ad%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20many%20direct%20reports%20is%20too%20many%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENvidia%20CEO%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnvidia-hardcore-intensity-culture-mission-driven-jensen-huang-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20Jensen%20Huang%3C%2Fa%3E%20famously%20has%2060%20direct%20reports.%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdell-reorganizes-top-ranks-asks-senior-managers-lead-more-staff-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20Managers%20at%20Dell%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20been%20told%20they%20should%20have%2015%20to%2020.%20An%20AWS%20document%20viewed%20by%20BI%20in%20January%20mandated%20no%20fewer%20than%20eight%20per%20manager%2C%20up%20from%20six.%20An%20Amazon%20spokesperson%20told%20BI%20there%20are%20no%20such%20requirements%20companywide.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGallup%20research%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gallup.com%2Fworkplace%2F286997%2Fideal-team-size-depends-manager.aspx%3Futm_source%3Dchatgpt.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eindicates%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20quality%20of%20a%20manager%20matters%20more%20than%20the%20number%20of%20direct%20reports%20in%20terms%20of%20how%20well%20teams%20perform.%20That's%20because%20more%20engaged%20managers%20tend%20to%20lead%20to%20more%20engaged%20teams.%20And%20small%20teams%20%E2%80%94%20those%20with%20fewer%20than%2010%20people%20%E2%80%94%20show%20both%20the%20highest%20and%20lowest%20levels%20of%20engagement%20because%20managers%20can%20have%20an%20outsize%20effect%2C%20for%20better%20or%20worse.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20may%20explain%20why%20some%20companies%20seem%20to%20thrive%20with%20dozens%20of%20direct%20reports%20per%20manager%20and%20others%20fail.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20nature%20of%20the%20work%20matters%2C%20too.%20When%20work%20is%20more%20complex%2C%20it%20can%20be%20harder%20for%20managers%20to%20oversee%20too%20many%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EManaging%20dozens%20of%20people%20gets%20harder%20when%20%26quot%3Blife%20intersects%20with%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20Ravin%20Jesuthasan%2C%20the%20global%20leader%20for%20transformation%20services%20at%20the%20consulting%20firm%20Mercer%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20employees%20have%20an%20issue%2C%20they%20often%20need%20someone%20to%20talk%20to%20about%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20a%20manager%2C%20you%20are%20the%20first%20port%20of%20call%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20one%20reason%2C%20Jesuthasan%20said%2C%20that%20having%20something%20like%2020%20direct%20reports%20would%20likely%20be%20%26quot%3Breally%20hard.%26quot%3B%20For%20most%20managers%2C%20the%20couple%20of%20dozen%20direct%20reports%20that%20many%20tech%20companies%20are%20aiming%20for%20is%20probably%20the%20limit%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStrong%20managers%20can%20powerfully%20boost%20a%20company's%20ability%20to%20develop%20talent%20and%20its%20bottom%20line.%20A%202023%20analysis%20from%20McKinsey%20%26amp%3B%20Company%2C%20for%20example%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mckinsey.com%2Fcapabilities%2Fpeople-and-organizational-performance%2Four-insights%2Finvesting-in-middle-managers-pays-off-literally%3Futm_source%3Dchatgpt.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efound%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20organizations%20with%20%26quot%3Btop-performing%26quot%3B%20managers%20led%20to%20significantly%20better%20total%20shareholder%20returns%20over%20five%20years%20compared%20with%20those%20entities%20that%20had%20only%20average%20or%20subpar%20managers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20flattening%20schemes%20may%20be%20successful%20at%20reducing%20bulk%20in%20the%20middle%20and%20speeding%20up%20decision-making%2C%20they%20can%20hinder%20future%20growth%20if%20they're%20not%20well-managed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJane%20Edison%20Stevenson%2C%20global%20vice%20chair%20for%20board%20and%20CEO%20services%20at%20the%20organizational%20consulting%20firm%20Korn%20Ferry%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20removing%20layers%20from%20a%20management%20pyramid%20can%20help%20elevate%20those%20high%20performers.%20But%20flatter%20companies%20may%20fail%20to%20develop%20leaders%20who%20can%20pull%20together%20the%20disparate%20parts%20of%20an%20organization.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20some%20point%2C%20she%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BYou've%20got%20to%20start%20to%20make%20a%20bet%20on%20the%20leaders%20that%20are%20going%20to%20have%20a%20chance%20to%20build%20muscle%20across%2C%20not%20just%20vertically.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-amazon-google-embrace-flatter-structure-fewer-managers-boost-efficiency-2025-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1747645201000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F682799463fe8d39283662090%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-amazon-google-embrace-flatter-structure-fewer-managers-boost-efficiency-2025-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Tech%20giants%20like%20Microsoft%2C%20Amazon%2C%20and%20Google%20are%20cutting%20managers%20to%20increase%20efficiency%20and%20speed.%20But%20how%20many%20direct%20reports%20is%20too%20many%3F%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22ecosgrove%40businessinsider.com%20(Emma%20Cosgrove%2CTim%20Paradis%2CEugene%20Kim%2CAshley%20Stewart)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-