of%20New%20York.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Femployees-stuck-job-search-hiring-work-trump-tariffs-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EPresident%20Donald%20Trump's%20tariffs%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20creating%20uncertainty%20in%20the%20market%20and%20discouraging%20employers%20from%20hiring%20new%20workers%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhite-collar-recession-hiring-slump-jobs-tech-industry-applications-rejection-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ewhite-collar%20workers%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20feeling%20stuck%20in%20their%20roles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fblue-collar-job-demand-growth-white-collar-layoffs-ai-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eblue-collar%20jobs%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20some%20of%20which%20pay%20a%20stable%20six%20figures%20%E2%80%94%20are%20starting%20to%20look%20more%20like%20an%20oasis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20proportion%20of%20students%20at%20two-year%20colleges%20focusing%20on%20vocational%20studies%20compared%20to%20other%20associate%20degrees%20grew%20from%20about%2015%25%20in%202019%20to%20nearly%2020%25%20in%202024%2C%20according%20to%20the%20National%20Student%20Clearinghouse%20Research%20Center.%20The%20fastest-growing%20jobs%20in%20the%20country%2C%20per%20the%20US%20Bureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics%2C%20are%20wind%20turbine%20technicians%20and%20solar%20panel%20installers%2C%20followed%20by%20roles%20in%20healthcare%20and%20some%20in%20tech%2C%20like%20data%20analysts%20or%20information%20security%20analysts.%20Jobs%20in%20construction%2C%20plumbing%2C%20electrical%20work%2C%20and%20transportation%20are%20all%20projected%20to%20grow%20faster%20than%20the%20average%20job-growth%20rate%20of%204%25%20from%202023%20to%202033.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20need%20for%20workers%20in%20renewable%20energy%2C%20commercial%20and%20home%20construction%2C%20and%20public%20infrastructure%20is%20expected%20to%20rise%2C%20thanks%20to%20projects%20like%20the%20Bipartisan%20Infrastructure%20Act%20and%20a%20global%20investment%20in%20new%20energy%20sources.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhousing-crisis-national-shortage-construction-workers-job-demand-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EHome%20prices%20are%20soaring%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20part%20thanks%20to%20construction%20worker%20shortages%2C%20and%20wages%20for%20those%20workers%20are%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20just%20as%20demand%20is%20increasing%2C%20a%20swath%20of%20skilled%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbaby-boomer-gen-z-millennials-economy-housing-job-market-stocks-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ebaby%20boomer%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20laborers%20are%20getting%20ready%20to%20pack%20it%20up%20and%20retire.%20That%20will%20open%20up%20more%20gigs%20for%20people%20who%20want%20to%20work%20in%20these%20in-demand%2C%20automation-proof%20roles%20such%20as%20HVAC%20servicing%2C%20plumbing%2C%20and%20construction%20%E2%80%94%20and%20it's%20unlikely%20you'll%20hire%20a%20robot%20to%20come%20fiddle%20with%20your%20home's%20electrical%20wiring%20anytime%20soon.%20In%20fact%2C%20many%20analysts%20predict%20these%20fields%20could%20experience%20labor%20shortages%2C%20which%20is%20good%20news%20for%20Gen%20Z.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20where%20generative%20AI%20is%20stagnating%20growth%20in%20industries%20like%20tech%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flanding-dream-jobs-tech-consulting-banking-are-harder-than-ever-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Econsulting%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20it's%20accelerating%20growth%20for%20young%20people%20who%20want%20to%20start%20their%20own%20businesses.%20ChatGPT%20and%20its%20ilk%20have%20become%20always-on%20assistants%20that%20help%20young%20entrepreneurs%20automate%20work%20like%20appointment%20scheduling%20and%20generating%20emails%20to%20customers%20%E2%80%94%20and%20they%20don't%20have%20to%20be%20put%20on%20payroll.%20And%20as%20the%20digital-first%20generation%2C%20Gen%20Z%20doesn't%20need%20school%20to%20train%20them%20on%20the%20kind%20of%20tech%20that%20can%20make%20these%20businesses%20more%20efficient.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey're%20very%20used%20to%20working%20with%20technology%3B%20it's%20part%20of%20their%20daily%20life%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Gary%20Specter%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20Simpro%2C%20which%20makes%20job%20and%20project%20management%20software%20for%20field%20service%20and%20trade%20contracting%20industries.%26quot%3BYou're%20seeing%20a%20coming%20together%20of%20technology%20and%20these%20hands-on%20jobs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20some%2C%20a%20blue-collar%20pivot%20would%20mean%20abandoning%20the%20college%20dreams%20laid%20out%20by%20parents%2C%20siblings%2C%20and%20countless%20coming-of-age%20movies.%20As%20America's%20middle%20class%20grew%2C%20so%20did%20the%20drive%20for%20higher%20education.%20In%201970%2C%20just%2011%25%20of%20US%20adults%20had%20a%20bachelor's%20degree.%20By%202021%2C%20that%20number%20had%20swelled%20to%2038%25%2C%20according%20to%20US%20Census%20data.%20Sending%20kids%20to%20a%20university%20became%20less%20a%20privilege%20and%20more%20a%20given%20for%20many%20middle-class%20families.%20But%20that%20push%20ignored%20other%20viable%20career%20paths%20and%20gave%20rise%20to%20a%20stigma%20around%20blue-collar%20work%20that%20persists%20today%2C%20even%20as%20rising%20tuition%20costs%20have%20dampened%20the%20appeal%20of%20the%20college%20dream.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERyan%20Daniels%2C%2022%2C%20left%20behind%20college%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Florida%20after%20his%20freshman%20year%20in%202022%20to%20pursue%20his%20pressure-washing%20business%20full%20time.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20really%20shocking%20to%20people%20that%20I%20was%20going%20to%20let%20that%20opportunity%20go%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20tells%20me.%20But%20he's%20not%20alone%20in%20that%20shift.%20The%20rate%20of%20young%20people%20enrolled%20in%20college%20dropped%20from%2041%25%20in%202012%20to%2039%25%20in%202022%2C%20according%20to%20the%20National%20Center%20for%20Education%20Statistics.%20Enrollment%20in%20college%20peaked%20in%202010%2C%20but%20has%20since%20declined%20from%2018%20million%20students%20to%20about%2015.4%20million%20in%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGetting%20young%20people%20into%20the%20trades%20will%20still%20take%20a%20mindset%20shift.%20In%20a%202023%20survey%20of%20US%20high%20schoolers%20by%20Jobber%2C%20a%20software%20for%20home%20professionals%2C%2074%25%20said%20they%20thought%20there%20was%20a%20stigma%20around%20choosing%20vocational%20school%20instead%20of%20a%20four-year%20college%2C%20and%2079%25%20said%20their%20parents%20wanted%20them%20to%20go%20to%20college%2C%20while%20only%205%25%20said%20their%20parents%20encouraged%20vocational%20school.%20A%20Gallup%20survey%20found%20that%20around%2070%25%20of%20high%20school%20students%20had%20heard%20a%20lot%20about%20college%2C%20while%20less%20than%20a%20quarter%20had%20heard%20frequently%20about%20apprenticeships%20and%20vocational%20schools.%20And%20it%20may%20be%20blue-collar%20influencers%2C%20rather%20than%20a%20vocational%20school%20rep%20at%20an%20assembly%2C%20who%20pull%20more%20young%20people%20into%20these%20fields.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGen%20Z%20really%20is%20facing%20a%20new%20set%20of%20challenges%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Jennifer%20Herrity%2C%20who%20follows%20career%20trends%20at%20Indeed.%20%26quot%3BSocial%20media%20has%20really%20introduced%20Gen%20Z%20to%20what%20working%20in%20new%20fields%20can%20be%20like.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDay-in-the-life%20videos%20have%20flooded%20YouTube%2C%20TikTok%2C%20and%20Instagram%2C%20giving%20people%20a%20peek%20into%20careers%20that%20many%20may%20not%20have%20known%20about%20unless%20a%20family%20member%20worked%20in%20them.%20There%20are%20some%20that%20show%20consultants%20or%20tech%20workers%20shuttling%20from%20an%20early%20morning%20at%20Equinox%20to%20their%20offices%20and%20then%20from%20meeting%20to%20meeting%2C%20%249%20matcha%20latte%20in%20hand%2C%20but%20the%20more%20visually%20interesting%20videos%20come%20from%20people%20doing%20hands-on%20work%20in%20their%20fields.%20There%20are%20electricians%2C%20plumbers%2C%20landscapers%2C%20and%20more%20who%20show%20themselves%20out%20in%20the%20wild%20getting%20their%20complicated%20jobs%20done.%20Osburn%20tells%20me%20he%20watched%20videos%20on%20social%20media%20about%20starting%20his%20landscape%20business.%20Now%2C%20he%20has%2045%2C000%20followers%20watching%20him%20on%20Instagram%20as%20he%20drives%20his%20trucks%20around%20Virginia%20.%20Lexi%20Abreu%2C%20an%20electrician%20with%20200%2C000%20followers%20on%20YouTube%2C%20walks%20viewers%20through%20tricky%20wiring%20jobs%20and%20makes%20tongue-in-cheek%20visual%20gags%20about%20working%20as%20a%20woman%20in%20a%20male-dominated%20profession.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20college%20kids%20pinch%20pennies%2C%20those%20who%20go%20into%20trades%20can%20start%20earning%20immediately.%20Average%20entry-level%20construction%20jobs%20start%20at%20around%20%2419%20an%20hour%2C%20and%20rise%20to%20%2445%20at%20the%20top%20level%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Bureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics.%20Maintenance%20and%20repair%20jobs%20start%20around%20%2414%20an%20hour%20but%20can%20go%20as%20high%20as%20%2444%20an%20hour.%20The%20average%20electrician%20and%20plumber%20make%20about%20%2429%20an%20hour%2C%20according%20to%20Indeed.%20Instead%20of%20surviving%20on%20cup%20noodles%20for%20four%20years%2C%20Daniels%20has%20built%20a%20business%2C%20RHI%20Pressure%20Washing%2C%20and%20can%20pay%20not%20just%20his%20own%20bills%2C%20but%20those%20of%20three%20employees.%20Already%2C%20people%20are%20increasingly%20seeing%20the%20value%20of%20working%20in%20the%20trades.%20In%202024%2C%2066%25%20of%20adults%20said%20they%20believed%20there%20were%20well-paid%2C%20stable%20jobs%20available%20to%20those%20with%20only%20high%20school%20diplomas%20or%20GEDs%2C%20up%20from%2050%25%20in%202018%2C%20a%20survey%20of%20about%201%2C500%20people%20conducted%20by%20the%20think%20tank%20New%20America%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20blue-collar%20perks%20don't%20mean%20college%20degrees%20are%20dying%20anytime%20soon.%20The%20median%20pay%20for%20a%20Gen%20Z%20college%20graduate%20in%202024%20was%20%2460%2C000%2C%20based%20on%20data%20from%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20New%20York%2C%20compared%20to%20%2440%2C000%20for%20a%20high%20school%20graduate.%20That%20gap%20widens%20as%20college-educated%20workers%20age%20and%20advance%20through%20their%20fields.%20And%20some%20of%20these%20stable%20fields%20are%20hiring%20for%20college%20grads%2C%20too%3A%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffastest-growing-jobs-college-graduates-construction-oil-gas-utilities-linkedin-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Efastest-growing%20industry%20for%20new%20college%20grads%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20in%20construction%2C%20LinkedIn%20says%2C%20and%20entry-level%20workers%20are%20also%20rising%20in%20number%20in%20the%20utility%20sector%20and%20oil%2C%20gas%2C%20and%20mining%20industries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDaniels%20would%20have%20graduated%20from%20college%20this%20month%2C%20but%20in%20that%20time%2C%20he%20has%20instead%20spun%20out%20his%20high%20school%20side%20hustle%20of%20pressure%20washing%20into%20a%20full%20business.%20He%20spends%20most%20of%20his%20day%20running%20the%20business%20side.%20That%20means%20using%20ChatGPT%20almost%20daily%2C%20whether%20it's%20to%20draft%20responses%20to%20customers%20or%20mass%20emails%2C%20Daniels%20says.%20Gen%20AI%20might%20%26quot%3Btake%20away%20from%20white-collar%20jobs%2C%20and%20it%20really%20helps%20us%20out%20here.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fama